      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "docs: remove turnkey hosting service docs",
        "body": "Related: #94584\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nResolves a docs placement problem where the public hosting docs promoted turnkey third-party OpenClaw hosting paths after maintainers decided core docs should not endorse third-party hosting services.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThe hosting docs now focus on infrastructure users administer themselves. Hostinger is kept as a self-managed VPS guide, the hosted-template pages for Railway, Northflank, Render, and Upstash Box are removed from the docs source, and their old routes now redirect to the generic Linux server guide.\n\nThis PR was prepared with Codex.\n\n## User Impact\n\nUsers can still find VPS, VM, container, Kubernetes, and local server hosting guidance, including a Hostinger VPS path. They will no longer be routed from OpenClaw docs to turnkey third-party service pages.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `pnpm docs:list`\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 docs\\vps.md docs\\install\\hostinger.md docs\\install\\index.md`\n- `pnpm docs:check-mdx`\n- `pnpm docs:check-links`\n- `pnpm docs:check-i18n-glossary`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `node -e \"JSON.parse(require('fs').readFileSync('docs/docs.json','utf8')); console.log('docs.json ok')\"`",
